    "question_id" : 35231291,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you use gradle you can just add</p>\n<pre><code>org.gradle.jvmargs=-Dfile.encoding=UTF-8\n</code></pre>\n<p>to your <code>%userprofile%\\\\.gradle\\gradle.properties</code> file (or <code>gradle.properties</code> on project level).</p>\n<p>Ref.: <a href=\"https://docs.gradle.org/current/userguide/common_caching_problems.html#system_file_encoding\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://docs.gradle.org/current/userguide/common_caching_problems.html#system_file_encoding</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11566757,
      "reputation" : 51,
      "user_id" : 8474774,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/JzJR0.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Andrey S",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8474774/andrey-s"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1700308711,
    "creation_date" : 1700308711,
    "answer_id" : 77506790,
    "question_id" : 35231291,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This helps me:</p>\n<p>By default, IntelliJ IDEA uses the system encoding to view console output.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>In the <strong>Settings</strong> dialog (Ctrl + Alt + S), select <strong>Editor</strong> | <strong>General</strong> | <strong>Console</strong>.</li>\n<li>Select the default encoding from the <strong>Default Encoding</strong> list.</li>\n<li>Click <strong>OK</strong> to apply the changes.</li>\n<li>Reopen your console.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>From <a href=\"https://www.jetbrains.com/help/idea/encoding.html#file-encoding-settings\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">jetbrains.com</a></p>\n"
  }, {
